import React from 'react'; const Resume = () => { return (

Deepthi De Silva

Contact: 0418 845 259

Email: desilvadeepthi@yahoo.com.au

Career Objective

I take pride in my work and have attention to detail. Presently, I am looking for a full-time IT Support/Administration role in an educational environment. My employment experience and education have enabled me to develop a quality administration skill set - in the form of organizing and scheduling events, manipulating DBMS (Database Management System), editing, formatting, and presentation of the required information. Similarly, I have experience in teaching and customer service.

Key Competencies

  • Mature and professional approach with proven ability to manage complex tasks through to completion
  • High level of computer literacy with strong MS Office skills, including Word, Excel, Access, PowerPoint, and Notepad. Thorough knowledge of graphic software, such as 3ds Max and Flash MX. Strong knowledge of analyzing data to find standard deviation, mean, median, and mode. Able to modify computer programming code.
  • Excellent communication skills with the ability to liaise with people from all levels
  • Highly organized with the ability to prioritize multiple tasks and meet deadlines
  • Strong team spirit and the ability to work harmoniously in a team environment
  • Proactive manner with strong organizational skills and ability to prioritize

Employment Experience

Primary Schools (Multiple) — 2008 – 2018

Admin/Student Teacher Placement

Job Responsibilities:

  • Managed student behavior by reinforcing the teacher’s instructions with repetition catered to various learning styles
  • Communicated with teachers about organized classroom layout and resources to support classroom teachers, whilst building rapport with students
  • Determined work priorities, schedule, and approach to be aligned with school and management policies
  • Followed WHS policies & procedures to ensure a safe learning environment for students and teachers
  • Self-motivated to complete set tasks before deadlines and proactively prepared myself and organized resources for lessons

Accomplishments:

  • Developed and learned how the curriculum and school systems operate and provide strategic learning outcomes for specific age groups of children
  • Learned to communicate with staff around tasks that need to be prioritized by negotiation in an informative and friendly manner built on trust
  • Worked with several schools such as Brandon Park, Chalcot Lodge, Narre Warren Primary School, Brunswick Secondary College; quickly established rapport when meeting new people.

Kapruka Money Transferring — 2005 - 2007

Administration Officer

Job Responsibilities:

  • Constructed and administered invoices, bankruptcy notices, debt recovery, and service of notices
  • Facilitated ongoing administrative support through excellent time management and high attention to detail to uphold continuous improvement within the business
  • Handled and resolved customer inquiries by ensuring to provide the best and effective advice
  • Served customers using five-step customer service standards
  • Operated the cash register for all cash, EFTPOS, and credit card purchases, refunds, and exchanges
  • Maintained the customer and banking databases accurately by entering the data, conducting daily backups including digital and paper copies
  • Responsible for ensuring all relevant financial reports were checked, any discrepancies were investigated, and reported to the company Director

Accomplishments:

  • Managed the accurate and timely processing of up to 1,200 money transfers ($200,000) per month through attention to detail and application of processing
  • Developed communication skills to provide customer service to a wide range of people from different cultural backgrounds

St. Joseph’s College (Sri Lanka) — 1996-2005

Teacher/IT Coordinator

Job Responsibilities:

  • Prepared course materials according to Ministry of Education system guidelines
  • Conducted classes through formal lessons, discussions, practical activities, projects, and assignments
  • Set tests, exams, projects, assignments, and homework; corrected and collated results
  • Developed courses and instructional materials including visual aids, student handouts, and reference materials
  • Participated in school holiday programs, arranged school excursions, drama, and sports competitions
  • Provided computer technical and instructional support to students while troubleshooting the management/maintenance of equipment including computers, printers, and scanners
  • Installed and updated software and troubleshot software problems to ensure efficiency and work productivity

Accomplishments:

  • Trained the instructors and managed the administration side of the computer division; maintained student databases and library databases, generated reports according to school authorities' requirements, use of hardware, network, and other technology

Education & Training

  • Diploma of Information Technology [Advanced Programming] (2023-2024) - Holmesglen Institute of TAFE
  • Diploma of Web Development (2022) - Holmesglen Institute of TAFE
  • Certificate IV Web Development (2021) - Holmesglen Institute of TAFE
  • Diploma of Early Childhood Education and Care (2016) - Swinburne University
  • Certificate of Education Support (Integration Aide/Teacher Aide) (2013) - Monash University
  • Bachelor of Science and Education (P-12) (2012) - RMIT University
); }; export default Resume;
